Acceleration in Data Federation

Acceleration retrieves data from the source and persists it as an Accelerated data lake object (DLO) in Data Cloud. Acceleration eliminates the risk of potential timeouts or run-time latencies. You can refresh the persisted data at your preferred frequency.

Acceleration is turned on by default when you create a data stream, but you can disable or enable it at any time by editing the data stream. You can refresh all objects with a data-time field incrementally and as frequently as every 15 minutes. An incremental refresh updates the accelerated DLO with data that was added or changed since the last refresh, but it doesn’t update deleted data.

To enable an incremental refresh, choose the desired record modified field, which denotes the timestamp for the incremental refresh, and the desired frequency. If the chosen frequency is more than or equal to 24 hours, you can then choose a desired refresh time and day. Incremental refresh currently supports upserts and doesn't support deletes. The accelerated DLO is updated with data added or changed since the last refresh.

You can also retrieve data in full refresh mode. When you opt for a full refresh, during each refresh cycle, all the existing data is deleted and replaced with the newly imported dataset.

TIP To keep your data fresh and in sync with your data source, perform a full refresh at regular intervals.
